sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS num_users
FROM reviews
WHERE review_id > (SELECT AVG(review_count) FROM users);

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM moderation
WHERE moderator_id = 1;

SELECT restaurant_id, COUNT(review_id) AS total_reviews
FROM reviews
GROUP BY restaurant_id;

external_knowledge:
- "travelers" metaphorically refers to users;
- "navigating the murky waters of flagged content" refers to users whose reviews have been flagged;
- "where they cast their virtual anchors" metaphorically refers to the locations of these users.

